[
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The sovereign "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " showed me this: I saw"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " a basket of summer fruit."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He said, “What do you see, Amos?” I replied, “A basket of summer fruit.” Then the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " said to me, “The end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " has come for my people Israel! I will no longer overlook their sins."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The women singing in the temple"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " will wail in that day.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "The sovereign "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " is speaking. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“There will be many corpses littered everywhere!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Be quiet!” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Listen to this, you who trample"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the needy,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "and do away with"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the destitute in the land."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " You say, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“When will the new moon festival"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " be over,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " so we can sell grain? "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "When will the Sabbath end,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " so we can open up the grain bins?"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "We’re eager"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to sell less for a higher price,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "and to cheat the buyer with rigged scales!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " We’re eager to trade silver for the poor,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "a pair of sandals"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " for the needy!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "We want to mix in some chaff with the grain!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " confirms this oath"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " by the arrogance of Jacob:"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“I swear"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " I will never forget all you have done!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Because of this the earth"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " will quake,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "and all who live in it will mourn."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "The whole earth"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " will rise like the River Nile,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "it will surge upward"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and then grow calm,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " like the Nile in Egypt."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " In that day,” says the sovereign "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", “I will make the sun set at noon,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "and make the earth dark in the middle of the day."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " I will turn your festivals into funerals,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "and all your songs into funeral dirges."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "I will make everyone wear funeral clothes"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "and cause every head to be shaved bald."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "I will make you mourn as if you had lost your only son;"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "when it ends it will indeed have been a bitter day."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Be certain of this,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the time is"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " coming,” says the sovereign "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“when I will send a famine through the land – "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "not a shortage of food or water"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "but an end to divine revelation!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " People"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " will stagger from sea to sea,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "and from the north around to the east. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "They will wander about looking for a revelation from"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "but they will not find any."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " In that day your"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " beautiful young women"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and your"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " young men will faint from thirst."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " These are the ones who now take oaths"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " in the name of the sinful idol goddess"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of Samaria. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "They vow,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " ‘As surely as your god"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " lives, O Dan,’ or ‘As surely as your beloved one"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " lives, O Beer Sheba!’ "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "But they will fall down and not get up again.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  }
]